      • getSystemAndEcuInstance

        public static Pair<IEntity,IEntity> getSystemAndEcuInstance(java.lang.String projectName,
                                                            java.lang.Class<? extends IEntity> clazz,
                                                            boolean openSelectionDialog,
                                                            APIOperationStatus status)
        Retrieve the System entity and the EcuInstance entity the user has selected in the project settings of the project with the given name. If the user has either not yet selected System and EcuInstance or the selected values are not valid anymore, the user will be queried to select System and EcuInstance if openSelectionDialog is true. If there are not systems available in the system model, then the user is asked if he wants to create one dummy System and EcuInstance from an existing top-level Composition. If no entities are available at all, or the user cancelled the dialog, or the project is not loaded, then null is returned.
        Parameters:
        projectName - The name of the project to query
        clazz - The type of the requested root entity, e.g. IAUTOSAR
        openSelectionDialog - true if the selectionDialog shall be shown, else false
        status - an error-status is added in case, null is returned
        Returns:
        Pair of system/ecuInstance or null (together with an error-status)
        Since:
        17.0
